Facebook, the world&rsquo;s largest online social media and networking firm, has launched a new software.The new app, Messenger Lite &ndash; a standalone version of Messenger for Android &ndash; is being rolled out in Kenya, Tunisia, Malaysia, Sri Lanka and Venezuela in the first phase.&ldquo;Messenger Lite is a slimmed down version of Messenger that offers the core features of Messenger for markets with slower than average Internet speeds,&rdquo; Engineering manager for Messenger Lite Tom Mulcahy said on a blog. &ldquo;With Messenger Lite, people are able to quickly and easily send texts, photos and links to anyone using Messenger or Messenger Lite.&rdquo;